  "prompt": "What causes hair loss for men?",
  "response": "Several factors can contribute to hair loss in men:\n\n1. Genetics (Androgenetic Alopecia)\n- Most common cause\n- Male pattern baldness\n- Inherited from family\n- Hormone-related\n\n2. Hormonal Changes\n- Testosterone conversion to dihydrotestosterone (DHT)\n- Shrinks hair follicles\n- Leads to gradual hair thinning\n\n3. Age\n- Natural hair thinning with aging\n- Decreased hair production\n- Slower hair growth\n\n4. Medical Conditions\n- Thyroid problems\n- Autoimmune diseases\n- Scalp infections\n- Alopecia areata\n\n5. Stress\n- Physical or emotional stress\n- Can trigger temporary hair loss\n- Telogen effluvium condition\n\n6. Nutritional Deficiencies\n- Lack of protein\n- Iron deficiency\n- Vitamin deficiencies\n\n7. Medications\n- Chemotherapy\n- Blood pressure medications\n- Steroids\n- Some antidepressants\n\n8. Lifestyle Factors\n- Poor diet\n- Smoking\n- Excessive alcohol consumption\n- Lack of sleep\n\n9. Excessive Hair Styling\n- Tight hairstyles\n- Chemical treatments\n- Heat damage\n\nTreatment options vary depending on the specific cause.",
